(482, 1, '2015-06-08 07:27:18', '2015-06-08 07:27:18', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3 class="tab-title">Course Description</h3>\r\n<div class="js-simple-collapse" data-more="Full details">\r\n<div class="js-simple-collapse-inner">\r\n\r\nDo you ever wish you could know what someone is thinking? Or perhaps you want to improve your own non-verbal communication? Body language is a great way to gain insights into how others think and feel, as well improve your everyday communication with others.\r\n\r\nThis body language course is based on scientifically-backed research, and is designed to teach you how to read people''s nonverbal behavior and improve your own.\r\n\r\nWhether you are a business owner, parent, spouse, employee, human resources director, teacher or student, this course will change the way you interact with those around you.\r\n\r\nIf you have ever interacted with another person, this course will be useful to you because our everyday interactions are filled with secret nonverbal cues just waiting to be uncovered.\r\n\r\nWhy Is Body Language Important?\r\n\r\nUp to 93% of our communication is nonverbal. However, we often only think about the words we say, not how we say them. In this course, we will review the face, the body and how it expresses emotions and even talk a little bit about the lie detection.\r\n\r\nIn the Secrets of Body Language I give real life examples and tons of practical tips that you will be able to use immediately.\r\n\r\nIf You Don''t Learn How to Decode Body Language Now, You''ll Hate Yourself Later\r\n\r\nAt one point you will be on a date, in a business meeting, or in a negotiation and wish you know how to read body language. Invest the time in this course and you will be happy to have a leg up on your communication in the future.\r\n\r\nIf you wish you could begin to unravel the mysteries of body language, then enroll today in Secrets of Body Language now!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text="Course certificates" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal"][stm_color_separator][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][stm_certificate image="1490"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][stm_certificate image="1490"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Course overview" font_container="tag:h3|text_align:left" google_fonts="font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal" css=".vc_custom_1436944848385{margin-bottom: 30px !important;}"][stm_course_lessons title=" Section 1: Introduction"][stm_course_lesson icon="fa-icon-stm_icon_teacher" badge="free" title="Introduction" meta="Preview" meta_icon="fa fa-youtube-play"]Here is a brief overview to the course and what you will learn![/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon="fa fa-female" badge="preview" title="Body Language Challenge " meta="Preview" meta_icon="fa fa-youtube-play"]I have 2 body language challenges for you:\r\n\r\n1. I want you to test your skills from the beginning to the end of the course. We are going to watch 2 videos now and then watch them again at the end of the course, where we will slow them down and dissect the body language.\r\n\r\n2. Sign-Up to get free practice videos to test your skills:\r\n\r\n<a class="external-link" href="http://www.scienceofpeople.com/subscribe" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer">ScienceofPeople.com</a>\r\n\r\nReply to the first email and<strong> tell me what your biggest body language challenges are.</strong>[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon="fa-icon-stm_icon_teacher" badge="quiz" title="Test your first skills" meta_icon="fa fa-pencil"]We want to separate students with same skills on groups[/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][stm_course_lessons title="Section 2: Foundations of Body Language"][stm_course_lesson icon="fa fa-male" title="Foundations of Body Language " meta="Practice" meta_icon="fa fa-angellist"]Let''s Review the foundations of where body language science comes from and how we study it.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon="fa fa-male" title="How the Brain Views the Body" meta="Practice" meta_icon="fa fa-angellist"]This video gives an overview of how the brain reads body language.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon="fa fa-male" title="Where Does Body Language Come From?" meta="Practice" meta_icon="fa fa-angellist"][/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][stm_course_lessons title="Section 3: The Face and Microexpressions"][stm_course_lesson icon="fa fa-child" badge="free" title="The Face and Microexpressions "][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon="fa fa-eye" badge="free" title="Eye Behavior "][/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon="fa fa-header" badge="free" title="Head Behavior"]Since we are starting at the top of the body, it is important to talk about some interesting head behavior and what it means in body language expression.[/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'The Secrets of Body  Language', 'Do you want to have more business success? Mastering body language is the missing ingredient for many business owners. Nonverbal communication can not only help you be more effective in your business dealings, but it can also give you an added edge above competitors.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'the-secrets-of-body-language', '', '', '2015-08-05 06:17:42', '2015-08-05 06:17:42', '', 0, 'http://masterstudy.stylemixthemes.com/demo/?post_type=product&#038;p=482', 0, 'product', '', 0);
